page.title: 09FULNECK VALLEY-A NATURE WALK
page.content: A stroll down{Sisters' Walk}at Fulneck leads you through parallel lines of Elm and Sycamore trees,some of the former having died of Dutch Elm Disease.Underfoot is pasture including buttercups,daisies and clover. This walk leads into{Sisters' {Wood,}a cool beechwood allowing shafts of light to fall through the branches onto nettles and old beech leaves and nuts on the floor. The wood falls gently onto a manicured golf course sloping further still down towards{Fulneck Beck.}The Beck is overgrown with grasses and flowers.In the beck trailing green hair swirls round the meanders,with surface insects in abundance.In the water are the larvae of midges and mayfly as well as leeches and snails.
